Enumeration Type Documentation

enum cds::memory_order

C++0x memory order enum.

At that moment, the compilers do not implement C++0x Memory Model proposal. Therefore, we need define C++0x memory_order enum in the CDS library.

Enumerator:
memory_order_relaxed 

relaxed memory semantics

memory_order_consume 

consume memory semantics

memory_order_acquire 

acquire memory semantics

memory_order_release 

release memory semantics

memory_order_acq_rel 

acquire-release memory semantics

memory_order_seq_cst 

sequentially consistent memory semantics

end_of_memory_order 

helper value, for test purpose only. Do not use directly
